Edmonton Street News, also known by its abbreviated letters ESN is a street newspaper based in Edmonton, Alberta, Canada. It was established in 2002 and is distributed on the streets of Edmonton and Calgary, (since August of 2010, when Calgary Street Talk, was discontinued), by the homeless, handicapped and underemployed in exchange for a donation.
vendors purchase papers at 50 cents a copy.
in 2012 the name changed to Alberta Street News.
